answers.body_markdown:
You can&#39;t use the same port in two different containers, you always have to expose a different port.

To configure ngnix you must install it on your host, then go to the folder: 

    /etc/ngnix/sites-enabled 

Then create a .conf file with the specifications that ngnix will use.
Example:

myapi.conf

    server {
      server_name mywebsite.com;
      access_log  /etc/nginx/mywebsite.log;

      location / {
          proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:9003;
          proxy_set_header Host $host;
          proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
      }
    }

In this example, all traffic that arrives through the site mywebsite.com will be directed to the container that has port 9003 exposed.
I hope I helped you

